<p>I would like to know if this use of StringBuffer does the same thing as my previous code, because SonarQube asks me not to use <code>+=</code> for appending strings.</p>  <p>My previous code :</p>  <pre><code>String sign = ""; if (value &lt; 0) {     sign.append("-"); } </code></pre>  <p>My new code with StringBuffer :</p>  <pre><code>StringBuffer sign = new StringBuffer(); sign.append(""); if (value &lt; 0) {     sign.append("-"); } </code></pre>  <p>Is this better this way ? </p>  <p>Thanks for your advices.</p>